<node CREATED="1373806925049" ID="ID_1294872482" MODIFIED="1373806926394" TEXT="E is compact if every open cover of E has a finite subcover. "/>
<node CREATED="1373806969222" ID="ID_519310945" MODIFIED="1373806971195" TEXT="Heine-Borel Theorem ">
<node CREATED="1373806974966" ID="ID_1750130072" MODIFIED="1373807031424" TEXT="1. (The Heine-Borel theorem) A set $E \in \mathbb{R}^{n}$ is compact if and only if  it is closed and bounded.  "/>
<node CREATED="1373807205936" ID="ID_1771861690" MODIFIED="1373807250629" TEXT="2. A set $E \in \mathbb{R}^{n}$ is compact if and only if every sequence of points of E  has a subsequence which converges to a point of E.  "/>
</node>
